[
    {
        "content": "<p>If <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span> is a monoid and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is a right <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>-set, the set of functions <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\to M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span> has a monoid structure, defined by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>f</mi><mi>g</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mi>g</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(fg)(x) = f(x) g(x f(x))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>. Does this have a name? Can it be expressed more abstractly?</p>\n<p>There is also a group version of this. If <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> is a group, and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is now a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span>-set, we can take the subset of those <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mspace></mspace><mspace width=\"0.1111111111111111em\"></mspace><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0.17em\"></mo><mtext> ⁣</mtext><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">:</mo><mspace width=\"0.3333333333333333em\"></mspace><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f\\colon X \\to G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace nobreak\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1111111111111111em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:-0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mrel\">:</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.3333333333333333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> such that the map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>↦</mo><mi>x</mi><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">x \\mapsto x f(x)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.522em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↦</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">x</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is invertible. This is then a subgroup of the above monoid.</p>",
        "id": 222834485,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Capriotti",
        "timestamp": 1610701891
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>When you say \"the set of functions\", are you referring to arbitrary set functions or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>-set homomorphisms?</p>",
        "id": 222841341,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610706811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Arbitrary functions</p>",
        "id": 222841435,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Capriotti",
        "timestamp": 1610706856
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So why does it matter that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is a right <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>-set?<br>\nIf you just consider sets <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>, this is a consequence of the fact that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Mon}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">M</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">n</span></span></span></span></span> is self-enriched and we have a free-forgetful adjunction between it and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Set}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">S</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">e</span><span class=\"mord mathrm\">t</span></span></span></span></span>. I don't have a nice name for the phenomenon, though.</p>",
        "id": 222841776,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610707141
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure what you mean. It matters that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is an <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span>-set because the action appears in the definition of the multiplication.</p>",
        "id": 222841832,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Capriotti",
        "timestamp": 1610707194
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"face palm\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f926\" role=\"img\" title=\"face palm\">:face_palm:</span> I can normally read, I swear</p>",
        "id": 222841965,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610707271
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll come back when I find something useful to say <span aria-label=\"relieved\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f60c\" role=\"img\" title=\"relieved\">:relieved:</span></p>",
        "id": 222842388,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610707609
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It feels like it should be somehow adjoint to a semi-direct product operation, but I can't quite formulate the setting in which that would be the case...</p>",
        "id": 222842801,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610707937
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is some kind of semi-direct product, but non-canonically. At least in the group case, which is ultimately what I'm interested in, it should be isomorphic to some kind of wreath product of stabilisers.</p>",
        "id": 222843132,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Capriotti",
        "timestamp": 1610708189
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder if something related to <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/a/96256/95129\">this construction</a> of the semi-direct product as an adjoint might give you a setting where the monoids/groups you describe come out naturally.</p>",
        "id": 222846034,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1610710249
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe the right thing to say is that Mon is Set-powered: you can take powers of a monoid where the exponent is a set.</p>",
        "id": 222904064,
        "sender_full_name": "Joe Moeller",
        "timestamp": 1610735906
    }
]